I think you have a reasonable theory, and I like it.  Except what I was referring to was the way using the box makes you suddenly more able to have psychic abilities, e.g. having more dreams that are &quot;visitations&quot; from the dead, or being more able to know right before your best friend is going to phone you, stuff like that.  Psychic abilities.  Why should using the box make stuff like that happen more easily?  Because it does, and it&#39;s weird!



--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;Tom&quot; &lt;Tom_Ray@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; The random sounds make it easier to hear spirit voices in your head.  I discovered this effect VISUALLY staining at rsndom dots on a viewing screen.   In the visual mode the spirit only has to suppress the light spots and enhance the dark spots that do not match the image it is sending----Light and dark spots on the screen that correspond to the image dont have to be modulated at all---the result is a SAVING of &quot;psychic energy&quot; on the observers part, perhaps not much, but enough to make the difference between seeing and NOT seeing, however.   Random sound would work the same way only the frequencies that did not match the sounds being sent would have to be blocked or replaced, the frequencies already present would NOT have to be modulated--so SOME energy is saved and not as much effort is needed to hear the entity.  Effectively enhancing one&#39;s innate abilities.  It a lot easier to hear a spirit sound if some of the waves are already in place, than it would be if you had to build the entire word from scratch.
